description:
Proper Japanese Title: ワンパンマン

Published in Japan by Shueisha, Licensed in English by Viz Media as One-Punch Man.

One-Punch Man started out in 2009 as a free webcomic by the author ONE, and after receiving millions of hits, the author was approached by Yusuke Murata (previously best known for drawing Eyeshield 21) and the two began a collaborated effort to recreate the series with Murata's art and release it digitally through Tonari no Young Jump (the online spin-off of Weekly Young Jump).

Though occasionally the work is promoted and released in the physical Young Jump magazine, it is primarily digital and these physical collections are the print versions of the remade series, even while the original webcomic remains freely available.
name: Onepunch-man

description:
Ongoing series by writer Kieron Gillen and artist Jamie McKelvie about a world where numerous gods get reincarnated into young men and women every 90 years, known as "The Recurrence", but only live thereafter for two years. While they're on earth, these gods behave like pop stars thus are celebrated and worshiped like teen idols, but are also feared and hated by others.

Among these 12 young gods are Amaterasu, Baal, Baphomet, Inanna, Luci (aka Lucifer), Minerva, Sakhmet, Tara, and the Morrigan. Then there is a mysterious old lady called Ananke, the "God of Fate" and caretaker of the young gods, and Laura, a normal teenager who admires these young gods and would do everything to be one of them.
